Lab 2 SOFE 3950 - The program myshell.c is a small shell program.

You can compile the shell program by typing 'make myshell', 
myshell is only confirmed to work on linux based operating systems (18.04 Ubuntu)

You can invoke the shell program with a command by typing ".\myshell <command>".

I/O redirection in UNIX allows for the redirection of inputted text and output results.
Output of the shell program can be redirected by the use of > and >>. The >> redirection
will append to the output destination if it already exists while > will truncate.

The supported commands are:

cd <directory>

    Change the current default directory to <directory>. 
    If the <directory> argument is not present, report the current directory. 
    If the directory does not exist an appropriate error should be reported. 
    This command should also change the PWD environment variable.

clr

    Clear the screen.

dir <directory>

    List the contents of directory <directory>.

environ 

    List all the environment strings.

echo <comment>

    Display <comment> on the display followed by a new line 
    (multiple spaces/tabs may be reduced to a single space).

help 

    Display this help manual using the more filter. 

pause 

    Pause operation of the shell until 'Enter' is pressed.

quit 

    Quit the shell.
